    <note type="biography">
        <p>Author and journalist. Worked on provincial journals, 1846–52. Proprietor and editor of the <hi rend="italic">Atlas</hi> from 1852; editor, from 1862, of the <hi rend="italic">Intellectual Observer</hi>, continued as the <hi rend="italic">Student</hi>, 1868–71. Wrote under the name Little John for the <hi rend="italic">Weekly Times.</hi> Author of popular science papers. Secretary of the Royal Microscopical Society; president, 1878.</p></note>
